headline: BBY Q2 Deep Dive: Mixed Category Performance and Margin Pressures Shape Outlook
summary: Electronics retailer Best Buy (NYSE:BBY) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 1.6% year on year to $9.44 billion. The company expects the full year’s revenue to be around $41.5 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.28 per share was 4.5% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
